 can get a head start on [another bank=E2=80=99s] exposure that we know is =
coming.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0The other bank Thompson referred to was another bank =
in the Large Banking Organizations portfolio that acquired a different dist=
ressed institution in March 2023 under circumstances similar to NYCB=E2=80=
=99s acquisition of Signature Bank that same month.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">Less than two hours after emailing his colleague, on January 29, 2=
024, between approximately 11:13 a.m. and 11:38 a.m., Thompson purchased a =
total of 1,600 out-of-the-money put option contracts with an expiration dat=
e of February 16, 2024 =E2=80=93 contracts that would allow Thompson to mak=
e money if NYCB=E2=80=99s stock price fell by the February 16 expiration da=
te =E2=80=93 in the Thompson Accounts at a total cost of approximately $14,=
495.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Thompson=E2=80=99s January 29 NYCB put=
 option purchases accounted for more than 99% of the total trading volume i=
n those put options on his purchase date.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">A senior supervisor at the Fed learned that one of the banks he=
 supervised would be =E2=80=9Cannouncing substantial, unexpected losses,=E2=
=80=9D so he allegedly=C2=A0<em>bought put options</em>. Incredible stuff!=
=C2=A0The news came out, the stock dropped, and Thompson sold the puts and =
=E2=80=9Cand obtained ill-gotten profits of approximately $505,527 =E2=80=
=93 representing a return of approximately 3,745.2% in less than a week.=E2=
=80=9D He allegedly manufactured a half-million-dollar bonus for himself fr=
om bad banking news.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously you ar=
e not supposed to do this, because insider trading is illegal, but I am jus=
t hung up on the incentives here. If you are an insider trading bank superv=
isor, you want drama. You don=E2=80=99t even care if it=E2=80=99s good or b=
ad, as long as it is dramatic and unexpected. Your incentives are much=C2=
=A0<em>worse=C2=A0</em>than the bankers=E2=80=99! Bankers are perhaps more =
willing to take risks with depositor money than is socially optimal, but th=
ey still prefer to make money.=C2=A0<em>You=C2=A0</em>don=E2=80=99t care! I=
